text.__SUMMARY__:
Corallus annulatus is a non-venomous boa species found in Central and South America. Three subspecies are currently recognized, including the nominate subspecies described here.
Common names: ringed tree boa, annulated tree boa, northern annulated tree boa.
text.Description: The color pattern consists of a brownish-red ground color overlaid with blackish rings or netlike reticulations.
text.Geographic range: Found in Central America in eastern Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua, Costa Rica, Panama. Also in South America in Pacific Colombia and northwestern Ecuador. The type locality given is "Costa Rica."
